================================================================================
Premake build system
================================================================================

This document explains how to build SDLU with the premake build system


================================================================================
Supported platforms
================================================================================

* Windows (Visual Studio, CodeBlocks)
* Linux
* Mac OS X
* Raspberry Pi


================================================================================
Features
================================================================================

+ Supports Visual Studio, CodeBlocks, XCode, GNU make
+ Very fast and lightweight
- Assumes all depencies can be found in the default paths


================================================================================
Usage
================================================================================

To use the premake build system, open a shell and type:

    $ cd /path/to/SDLU              # go to the SDLU source code directory
    $ premake4 [options] [action]   # generate project files

If SDL2 and SDL2_ttf are not installed in the default paths, or if you are using
Windows, then it's better to run premake in 'interactive' mode:

    $ cd /path/to/SDLU
    $ premake4 [options] [action] --interactive

Project files will be generated in the newly created "build" directory. The
built library can be found under "build/lib".

Run 'premake4 --help' to see what actions are available.


================================================================================
Options
================================================================================

* --interactive:                Run in interactive mode
* --enable-cxx:                 Build the cxx interface
* --with-sdl2-library:          Specify the full path to the SDL2 library
* --with-sdl2-ttf-library:      Specify the full path to the SDL2_ttf library
* --with-sdl2-include-dir:      Specify the directory of the SDL2 headers
* --with-sdl2-ttf-include-dir:  Specify the directory of the SDL2_ttf headers
* --with-tests                  Also build the SDLU test programs

For a list of all available options, run 'premake4 --help'.


